1byte=2bit
short: 2byte
int=4byte
long=8byte
float=4byte
double=8byte
char=2byte
boolean=1bit

docker exec -it java-container bash : use whenevr you want to run  java programm 
to execute commands inside container .

docker exec -it java-container javac filename.java
docker exec -it java-container java filename
IF THIS NOT WOKR USE THIS 
docker exec -w /workspace java-container javac FileName.java
docker exec -w /workspace java-container java FileName



How to use GIT
 git init   #Turns your folder into a Git repository.

#Connect to GitHub (one time per repo) Link your local repo to a GitHub repo.
git remote add origin <GitHub-repo-URL> #origin is the BY DEFAULT name of the remote repo.

 git add <filename> #Add files for tracking 
 #or
 git add .  #Add all files for tracking

    git commit -m "your commit message"  #Commit changes with a message
    git push -u origin master  #Push changes to the remote repo (main is the branch name)